==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indusial
<hw>In*du"sial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Indusium</er>.]</ety> <def>Of, pertaining to, or containing, the
petrified cases of the larv⟦ae⟧ of certain insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Indusial limestone</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>a
fresh-water limestone, largely composed of the agglomerated cases of
caddice worms, or larv⟦ae⟧ of caddice flies (<gen>Phryganea</gen>). It
is found in Miocene strata of Auvergne, France, and some other
localities.</cd></cs></p>

<p><ent>Indusiated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Indusiate</ent>⟦br⟧
